name: 23S rRNA pseudouridine746 synthase
comment: RluA is the sole protein responsible for the in vivo formation of 23S RNA pseudouridine746 [2]. The dual-specificity enzyme also catalyses the formation of uridine32 in tRNA [3]. cf. EC 5.4.99.28 (tRNA pseudouridine32 synthase).

orthologs.K06177: tRNA pseudouridine32 synthase / 23S rRNA pseudouridine746 synthase

references.title: Crystal structure of pseudouridine synthase RluA: indirect sequence readout through protein-induced RNA structure.
Functional effect of deletion and mutation of the Escherichia coli ribosomal RNA and tRNA pseudouridine synthase RluA.
A dual-specificity pseudouridine synthase: an Escherichia coli synthase purified and cloned on the basis of its specificity for psi 746 in 23S RNA is also specific for psi 32 in tRNA(phe).
